
Overview of noun gulp

The noun gulp has 2 senses (first 1 from tagged texts)
                                           
1. (2) gulp, draft, draught, swig -- (a large and hurried swallow; "he finished it at a single gulp")
2. gulp, gulping -- (a spasmodic reflex of the throat made as if in swallowing)

Overview of verb gulp

The verb gulp has 2 senses (first 2 from tagged texts)
                                           
1. (5) gulp, quaff, swig -- (to swallow hurriedly or greedily or in one draught; "The men gulped down their beers")
2. (1) gulp -- (utter or make a noise, as when swallowing too quickly; "He gulped for help after choking on a big piece of meat")
